HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 111
BY REPRESENTATIVE NEWELL
A RESOLUTION
To commemorate the one hundredth anniversary of New Hope Baptist Church.
WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize New Hope Baptist Church for its history
of spiritual service and to commemorate the church's one hundredth anniversary; and
WHEREAS, New Hope Baptist Church was founded on April 16, 1926, by the late
Reverend Dotson and was initially known as Original Solid Rock Baptist Church; and
WHEREAS, after Reverend Dotson's passing, Reverend Freddie H. Dunn accepted
the call to shepherd the congregation; under his leadership, the church's membership grew
considerably and created a need for a larger sanctuary; and
WHEREAS, New Hope relocated to its current sanctuary in 1965; Pastor Dunn
faithfully served the needs of the growing congregation and community and spearheaded the
construction of a church educational building, which was completed in November 1985; and
WHEREAS, Pastor Dunn served New Hope until his passing on February 23, 1988,
and one month later, Reverend John C. Raphael was appointed to serve as pastor; the
membership continued to grow under Pastor Raphael, and the church established additional
ministries and programs to serve the community; and
WHEREAS, during Pastor Raphael's tenure, New Hope acquired numerous
properties that currently house Imani Breakthrough Recovery Project, Circle of Hope and
Healing Grief Support Group, and Lion Tamer's Ministry; and
WHEREAS, Pastor Raphael dedicated twenty-five years of service to the church
before his passing on June 15, 2013; New Hope Baptist's current pastor, Reverend Jamaal
Weathersby, was appointed on July 26, 2013; and
WHEREAS, Pastor Weathersby is committed to empowering his congregation with
the tools needed to expand the reach of New Hope Baptist's ministry and follows a vision
to further serve the church and the surrounding community; and
