WHEREAS, Pastor Weathersby initiated plans for the construction of the JCR
Community Center in the fall of 2019; the project succeeded despite the challenges
presented by the COVID-19 pandemic, and in April 2024, the JCR Community Center
celebrated its grand opening; today, the center is used by organizations that empower youth
and uplift the broader community; and
WHEREAS, New Hope Baptist Church is most deserving of the highest recognition
for its century-long role as a beacon of faith, hope, service, and love in the Central City
neighborhood and throughout the New Orleans metropolitan area.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commemorate the one hundredth anniversary of New
Hope Baptist Church and does hereby extend sincere wishes that the church and its members
remain prosperous in all of their endeavors.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
